snippet.textDisplay:
it's 2020 and I'm still over here with my hands in my pockets: wondering why Microsoft hasn't made a deal with Steam. Imagine if Microsoft revealed the Xbox Series X and spoke about all of its features. They ask the audience "Do you like what you have seen today? How would you react if we told you we had one more feature crammed into this box?" Then the Steam Logo appears on the screen. "Not only will Series X have access to the Xbox library, but it also has Full Steam Support!


Playstation had a terrible reveal; they were talking to developers, not consumers. They really should have come out of the gate talking about fast load times, PSVR 2, and full backwards compatibility with PS4.


in all, I'm disappointed with both of them. I may just say fuck-it and start saving for a PC with decent VR capability.


Playstation, Playstation 2, Xbox 360, Playstation 4... Who knows where I will go from here. Obviously I have no problem flip-flopping.

it's 2020 and I'm still over here with my hands in my pockets: wondering why Microsoft hasn't made a deal with Steam. How would you react if we told you we had one more feature crammed into this box?" Then the Steam Logo appears on the screen. Playstation had a terrible reveal; they were talking to developers, not consumers. They really should have come out of the gate talking about fast load times, PSVR 2, and full backwards compatibility with PS4.

Playstation, Playstation 2, Xbox 360, Playstation 4... Who knows where I will go from here. Obviously I have no problem flip-flopping.
